summary: This dispatch details information provided by Francisco Luis Rodrigues Gonzales, a Cuban refugee, regarding resistance activity in Cuba. It includes details about the Revolutionary Student Directorate, sabotage activities, and a planned insurrection in the Sierra Maestra area. It also mentions the capture and imprisonment of group members, including two Americans from Guantanamo Naval Base.
title: WEB/PBRUEN - Resistance Activity in Cuba
recipient: Acting Chief, WE; Chief of Station, Madrid
